\begin<<1353>>equation<<1353>>
p(k|n\Lambda\Delta)=\frac<<1780>>\left(  n\Lambda\Delta\right)  ^<<1354>>k<<1354>><<1780>><<1355>>k!<<1355>><tex2html_comment_mark>1825
e^<<1356>>-n\Lambda\Delta<<1356>> \label<<1357>>eq:def_poisson<<1357>><tex2html_comment_mark>1826
\end<<1358>>equation<<1358>>
従って \begin<<2800>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2800>>$\Lambda$\end<<2801>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2801>>の不偏推<tex2html_comment_mark>1827
定量である\begin<<2802>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2802>>$\hat<<1359>>\Lambda<<1359>>=k/(n\Delta)$\end<<2803>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2803>><tex2html_comment_mark>1828
がデータから求め<tex2html_comment_mark>1829
られるヒストグラ<tex2html_comment_mark>1830
ムの高さである.
\begin<<3372>>tex2html_deferred<<3372>>\par\end<<3373>>tex2html_deferred<<3373>>
\subsection<<1360>>平均積分二乗誤<tex2html_comment_mark>1831
差及びコスト関数<tex2html_comment_mark>1832
の導入<<1360>><tex2html_comment_mark>1833
\begin<<3374>>tex2html_deferred<<3374>>\par\end<<3375>>tex2html_deferred<<3375>>
\begin<<1361>>equation<<1361>>
\mathcal<<1362>>MISE<<1362>>=\left\langle <<1844>>E_<<1363>>\Lambda<<1363>>\left[  <<1842>>\frac<<1364>>1<<1364>><<1365>>\Delta<<1365>>\int
_<<1366>>0<<1366>>^<<1367>>\Delta<<1367>><<1832>>(\,<<1781>>\lambda_<<1368>>t<<1368>>-\hat<<1369>>\Lambda<<1369>><<1781>>\,)^<<1370>>2<<1370>>dt<<1832>><<1842>>\right]  <<1844>>\right\rangle
\label<<1371>>MSE<<1371>><tex2html_comment_mark>1834
\end<<1372>>equation<<1372>>
ここで \begin<<2804>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2804>>$\left\langle \,\cdot\,\right\rangle $\end<<2805>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2805>>は<tex2html_comment_mark>1835
レート過程\begin<<2806>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2806>>$\lambda_<<1373>>t<<1373>>$\end<<2807>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2807>>の経<tex2html_comment_mark>1836
路によるアンサン<tex2html_comment_mark>1837
ブル平均を意味し, \begin<<2808>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2808>>$E_<<1374>>\Lambda
<<1374>>\left[  \,\cdot\,\right]  $\end<<2809>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2809>>はレート\begin<<2810>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2810>>$\lambda_<<1375>>t<<1375>><tex2html_comment_mark>1838
$\end<<2811>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2811>>の区間幅\begin<<2812>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2812>>$\Delta$\end<<2813>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2813>>内での<tex2html_comment_mark>1839
時間平均が\begin<<2814>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2814>>$\Lambda$\end<<2815>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2815>>であ<tex2html_comment_mark>1840
る場合のスパイク<tex2html_comment_mark>1841
数の条件付き確率<tex2html_comment_mark>1842
分布(式\ref<<1376>>eq:def_poisson<<1376>>)による<tex2html_comment_mark>1843
平均操作を表す.
\begin<<3376>>tex2html_deferred<<3376>>\par\end<<3377>>tex2html_deferred<<3377>>
MISEを区間幅\begin<<2816>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2816>>$\Delta$\end<<2817>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2817>>内での<tex2html_comment_mark>1844
レートのゆらぎと<tex2html_comment_mark>1845
スパイク生成のゆ<tex2html_comment_mark>1846
らぎに分割し, さら<tex2html_comment_mark>1847
に区間幅\begin<<2818>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2818>>$\Delta$\end<<2819>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2819>>の選択<tex2html_comment_mark>1848
に依らない項を除<tex2html_comment_mark>1849
いたコスト関数を<tex2html_comment_mark>1850
導入することがで<tex2html_comment_mark>1851
きる.
\begin<<1377>>align<<1377>>
C(\Delta)  ;SPMamp;  \equiv\mathcal<<1378>>E<<1378>>-\left\langle <<1833>>\left(  <<1782>>\lambda_<<1379>>t<<1379>><tex2html_comment_mark>1852
-\langle\Lambda\rangle<<1782>>\right)  ^<<1380>>2<<1380>><<1833>>\right\rangle \nonumber\\ 
;SPMamp;  =\left\langle E_<<1381>>\Lambda<<1381>>\left[  (\hat<<1382>>\Lambda<<1382>>-\Lambda)^<<1383>>2<<1383>>\right]
\right\rangle -\left\langle <<1783>>\left(  <<1384>>\Lambda-\langle\Lambda\rangle<<1384>>\right)
^<<1385>>2<<1385>><<1783>>\right\rangle \label<<1386>>cost<<1386>><tex2html_comment_mark>1853
\end<<1387>>align<<1387>>
式\ref<<1388>>cost<<1388>>は\begin<<2820>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2820>>$\Lambda$\end<<2821>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2821>>の分散を<tex2html_comment_mark>1854
第２項に含んでい<tex2html_comment_mark>1855
るので, 観測量のみ<tex2html_comment_mark>1856
からなる式に書き<tex2html_comment_mark>1857
直し次式を得る.
\begin<<1389>>equation<<1389>>
C\left(  \Delta\right)  =2\left\langle E_<<1390>>\Lambda<<1390>>\left[  (\hat<<1391>>\Lambda
<<1391>>-\Lambda)^<<1392>>2<<1392>>\right]  \right\rangle -\left\langle E_<<1393>>\Lambda<<1393>>\left[
(<<1784>>\hat<<1394>>\Lambda<<1394>>-\langle\Lambda\rangle<<1784>>)^<<1395>>2<<1395>>\right]  \right\rangle \label<<1396>>Cn<<1396>><tex2html_comment_mark>1858
\end<<1397>>equation<<1397>>
ヒストグラムの最<tex2html_comment_mark>1859
適区間幅決定の手<tex2html_comment_mark>1860
順を以下にまとめ,
図\ref<<1398>>CostFunction<<1398>>-aに(i)-(iv)の手順<tex2html_comment_mark>1861
から得られたコス<tex2html_comment_mark>1862
ト関数を示す.
\begin<<3378>>tex2html_deferred<<3378>>\par\end<<3379>>tex2html_deferred<<3379>>
\begin<<3380>>tex2html_deferred<<3380>>\bigskip\end<<3381>>tex2html_deferred<<3381>>
\begin<<3382>>tex2html_deferred<<3382>>\par\end<<3383>>tex2html_deferred<<3383>>
We consider sequences of spikes repeatedly recorded from a single neuron under
identical experimental conditions. A recent analysis revealed that \textit<<1399>>in
vivo<<1399>> spike trains are not simply random, but possess inter-spike-interval
distributions intrinsic and specific to individual neurons. However, spikes
accumulated from a large number of spike trains are in the majority mutually
independent, and can be regarded as being derived from a time-dependent
Poisson point process~\cite<<1400>>Snyder75,Daley88,Kass05<<1400>>.
\begin<<3384>>tex2html_deferred<<3384>>\par\end<<3385>>tex2html_deferred<<3385>>
\begin<<3386>>tex2html_deferred<<3386>>\bigskip\end<<3387>>tex2html_deferred<<3387>>推定量 \begin<<2822>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2822>>$\hat<<1401>>\lambda<<1401>>_<<1402>>t<<1402>>$\end<<2823>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2823>>と背<tex2html_comment_mark>1863
後のレート\begin<<2824>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2824>>$\lambda_<<1403>>t<<1403>>$\end<<2825>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2825>>
\begin<<3388>>tex2html_deferred<<3388>>\par\end<<3389>>tex2html_deferred<<3389>>
スパイク時系列の<tex2html_comment_mark>1864
レート\begin<<2826>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2826>>$\lambda_<<1404>>t<<1404>>$\end<<2827>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2827>>とヒスト<tex2html_comment_mark>1865
グラム \begin<<2828>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2828>>$\hat<<1405>>\lambda<<1405>>_<<1406>>t<<1406>>$\end<<2829>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2829>>\space の当て<tex2html_comment_mark>1866
はまりの良さは平<tex2html_comment_mark>1867
均積分二乗誤差(Mean Integrated
Squared Error, MISE)で評価する.
\begin<<1407>>equation<<1407>>
\mbox<<1408>>MISE<<1408>>\equiv\frac<<1409>>1<<1409>><<1410>>T<<1410>>\int_<<1411>>0<<1411>>^<<1412>>T<<1412>>E\,(\hat<<1413>>\lambda<<1413>>_<<1414>>t<<1414>>-\lambda_<<1415>>t<<1415>><tex2html_comment_mark>1868
)^<<1416>>2<<1416>>\,dt, \label<<1417>>eq:def_esterr<<1417>><tex2html_comment_mark>1869
\end<<1418>>equation<<1418>>
ここで\begin<<2830>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2830>>$E$\end<<2831>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2831>>はレート\begin<<2832>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2832>>$\lambda_<<1419>>t<<1419>><tex2html_comment_mark>1870
$\end<<2833>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2833>>の点過程から生成<tex2html_comment_mark>1871
されるサンプルに<tex2html_comment_mark>1872
ついて平均をとる<tex2html_comment_mark>1873
操作（期待値）を<tex2html_comment_mark>1874
意味する. ここで. We begin with a
bar-graph time histogram as \begin<<2834>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2834>>$\hat<<1420>>\lambda<<1420>>_<<1421>>t<<1421>>$\end<<2835>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2835>>, and explore a method to
select the bin size that minimizes the MISE. The difficulty of the present
problem comes from the fact that the underlying spike rate \begin<<2836>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2836>>$\lambda_<<1422>>t<<1422>>$\end<<2837>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2837>>\space is
not known.
\begin<<3390>>tex2html_deferred<<3390>>\par\end<<3391>>tex2html_deferred<<3391>>
\begin<<1423>>figure<<1423>>[h]
\begin<<1424>>center<<1424>>
\end<<1425>>center<<1425>>
\begin<<3392>>tex2html_deferred<<3392>>\caption<<1785>>The Bar-PSTH. A: an underlying spike rate, \begin<<2838>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2838>>$\lambda_<<1426>>t<<1426>>$\end<<2839>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2839>>. The
horizontal bars indicate the time averaged rates \begin<<2840>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2840>>$\theta$\end<<2841>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2841>>\space for individual bins
of width \begin<<2842>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2842>>$\Delta$\end<<2843>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2843>>. B: sequences of spikes derived from the underlying rate. C:
a time histogram for the sample sequences of spikes. The estimated rate
\begin<<2844>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2844>>$\hat<<1427>>\theta<<1427>>$\end<<2845>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2845>>\space is the total number of spikes \begin<<2846>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2846>>$k$\end<<2847>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2847>>\space that entered each bin,
divided by the number of sequences \begin<<2848>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2848>>$n$\end<<2849>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2849>>\space and the bin size \begin<<2850>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2850>>$\Delta$\end<<2851>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2851>>. <<1785>><tex2html_comment_mark>1878
\end<<3393>>tex2html_deferred<<3393>>\label<<1428>>BarSchematic<<1428>><tex2html_comment_mark>1879
\end<<1429>>figure<<1429>>
\begin<<3394>>tex2html_deferred<<3394>>\par\end<<3395>>tex2html_deferred<<3395>>
ヒストグラムは幅\begin<<2852>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2852>>$\Delta
$\end<<2853>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2853>>（ビン幅という）<tex2html_comment_mark>1881
の区間に含まれる<tex2html_comment_mark>1882
スパイクの数を数<tex2html_comment_mark>1883
えることで簡単に<tex2html_comment_mark>1884
作れる. is constructed simply by counting the number of
spikes that belong to each bin of width \begin<<2854>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2854>>$\Delta$\end<<2855>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2855>>. For an observation period
\begin<<2856>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2856>>$T$\end<<2857>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2857>>, we obtain \begin<<2858>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2858>>$N=\lfloor T/\Delta\rfloor$\end<<2859>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2859>>\space intervals. The number of spikes
accumulated from all \begin<<2860>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2860>>$n$\end<<2861>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2861>>\space sequences in the \begin<<2862>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2862>>$i$\end<<2863>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2863>>th interval is counted as \begin<<2864>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2864>>$k_<<1430>>i<<1430>><tex2html_comment_mark>1885
$\end<<2865>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2865>>. The bar height at the \begin<<2866>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2866>>$i$\end<<2867>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2867>>th bin is given as \begin<<2868>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2868>>$k_<<1431>>i<<1431>>/n\Delta$\end<<2869>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2869>>.
Figure~\ref<<1432>>BarSchematic<<1432>> shows the schematic diagram for the construction of
a bar-graph time histogram.
\begin<<3396>>tex2html_deferred<<3396>>\par\end<<3397>>tex2html_deferred<<3397>>
Given a bin of width \begin<<2870>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2870>>$\Delta$\end<<2871>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2871>>, the expected height of a bar graph for \begin<<2872>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2872>>$t
\in[0, \Delta]$\end<<2873>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2873>>\space is the time-averaged rate,
\begin<<1433>>equation<<1433>>
\theta= \frac<<1434>>1<<1434>><<1435>>\Delta<<1435>>\int_<<1436>>0<<1436>>^<<1437>>\Delta<<1437>><<1786>>\lambda_<<1438>>t<<1438>> \,dt<<1786>>.
\end<<1439>>equation<<1439>>
The total number of spikes \begin<<2874>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2874>>$k$\end<<2875>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2875>>\space from \begin<<2876>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2876>>$n$\end<<2877>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2877>>\space spike sequences that enter this bin of
width \begin<<2878>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2878>>$\Delta$\end<<2879>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2879>>\space obeys the Poisson distribution
\begin<<1440>>equation<<1440>>
p(k \,|\, n \Delta\theta) =\frac<<1787>>\left(  n \Delta\theta\right)  ^<<1441>>k<<1441>><<1787>><<1442>>k!<<1442>>
e^<<1443>>-n \Delta\theta<<1443>> \, , \label<<1444>>eq:def_poisson<<1444>><tex2html_comment_mark>1886
\end<<1445>>equation<<1445>>
whose expectation is \begin<<2880>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2880>>$n\Delta\theta$\end<<2881>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2881>>. The unbiased estimator for \begin<<2882>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2882>>$\theta$\end<<2883>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2883>>\space is
denoted as \begin<<2884>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2884>>$\hat<<1446>>\theta<<1446>>=k/(n\Delta)$\end<<2885>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2885>>, which is the empirical height of the
bar graph for \begin<<2886>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2886>>$t \in[0, \Delta]$\end<<2887>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2887>>.
\begin<<3398>>tex2html_deferred<<3398>>\par\end<<3399>>tex2html_deferred<<3399>>
\subsection<<1447>>Selection of the bin size<<1447>>
\begin<<3400>>tex2html_deferred<<3400>>\par\end<<3401>>tex2html_deferred<<3401>>
By segmenting the total observation period \begin<<2888>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2888>>$T$\end<<2889>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2889>>\space into \begin<<2890>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2890>>$N$\end<<2891>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2891>>\space intervals of size
\begin<<2892>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2892>>$\Delta$\end<<2893>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2893>>, the MISE defined in Eq.~\ref<<1448>>eq:def_esterr<<1448>> can be rewritten as
\begin<<1449>>equation<<1449>>
\label<<1450>>MISE1<<1450>>\mbox<<1451>>MISE<<1451>> = \frac<<1452>>1<<1452>><<1453>>\Delta<<1453>>\int_<<1454>>0<<1454>>^<<1455>>\Delta<<1455>>\frac<<1456>>1<<1456>><<1457>>N<<1457>>
\sum_<<1458>>i=1<<1458>>^<<1459>>N<<1459>> \, \left\{  E \, (\, <<1788>>\hat\theta_<<1460>>i<<1460>> - \lambda_<<1461>>t+(i-1)\Delta<<1461>>
<<1788>> \,)^<<1462>>2<<1462>> \right\}  \,dt,
\end<<1463>>equation<<1463>>
where \begin<<2894>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2894>>$\hat<<1464>>\theta<<1464>>_<<1465>>i<<1465>> \equiv k_<<1466>>i<<1466>>/(n\Delta)$\end<<2895>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2895>>. Hereafter we denote the
average over the segmented rate \begin<<2896>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2896>>$\lambda_<<1467>>t+(i-1)\Delta<<1467>>$\end<<2897>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2897>>\space as an average over
an ensemble of (segmented) rate functions \begin<<2898>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2898>>$\{ \lambda_<<1468>>t<<1468>> \}$\end<<2899>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2899>>\space defined on an
interval of \begin<<2900>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2900>>$t \in[0, \Delta]$\end<<2901>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2901>>, as
\begin<<1469>>equation<<1469>>
\mbox<<1470>>MISE<<1470>> =\frac<<1471>>1<<1471>><<1472>>\Delta<<1472>>\int_<<1473>>0<<1473>>^<<1474>>\Delta<<1474>>\left\langle <<1834>>E \, (\,
<<1789>>\hat\theta- \lambda_<<1475>>t<<1475>> <<1789>> \,)^<<1476>>2<<1476>> <<1834>> \right\rangle \,dt.
\end<<1477>>equation<<1477>>
The expectation \begin<<2902>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2902>>$E$\end<<2903>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2903>>\space refers to the average over the spike count, or
\begin<<2904>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2904>>$\hat<<1478>>\theta<<1478>>=k/(n\Delta)$\end<<2905>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2905>>, given a rate function \begin<<2906>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2906>>$\lambda_<<1479>>t<<1479>>$\end<<2907>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2907>>, or its mean
value \begin<<2908>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2908>>$\theta$\end<<2909>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2909>>.
\begin<<3402>>tex2html_deferred<<3402>>\par\end<<3403>>tex2html_deferred<<3403>>
The MISE can be decomposed into two parts,
\begin<<1480>>align<<1480>>
\mbox<<1481>>MISE<<1481>> = \left\langle <<1835>>E <<1790>>( <<1482>>\hat\theta- \theta<<1482>> )^<<1483>>2<<1483>> <<1790>> <<1835>> \right\rangle
+ \frac<<1484>>1<<1484>><<1485>>\Delta<<1485>>\int_<<1486>>0<<1486>>^<<1487>>\Delta<<1487>><<1843>>\left\langle <<1836>>\left(  <<1791>>\lambda_<<1488>>t<<1488>> -
\theta<<1791>> \right)  ^<<1489>>2<<1489>> <<1836>> \right\rangle dt<<1843>> . \label<<1490>>MISE2<<1490>><tex2html_comment_mark>1889
\end<<1491>>align<<1491>>
The first and second terms are, respectively, the stochastic fluctuation of
the estimator \begin<<2910>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2910>>$\hat<<1492>>\theta<<1492>>$\end<<2911>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2911>>\space around the expected mean rate \begin<<2912>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2912>>$\theta$\end<<2913>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2913>>, and the
averaged temporal fluctuation of \begin<<2914>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2914>>$\lambda_<<1493>>t<<1493>> $\end<<2915>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2915>>\space around its mean \begin<<2916>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2916>>$\theta$\end<<2917>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2917>>\space over
an interval of length \begin<<2918>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2918>>$\Delta$\end<<2919>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2919>>.
\begin<<3404>>tex2html_deferred<<3404>>\par\end<<3405>>tex2html_deferred<<3405>>
The second term of Eq.~\ref<<1494>>MISE2<<1494>> can further be decomposed into two parts,
\begin<<1495>>equation<<1495>>
\frac<<1496>>1<<1496>><<1497>>\Delta<<1497>>\int_<<1498>>0<<1498>>^<<1499>>\Delta<<1499>><<1792>>\left\langle ( \lambda_<<1500>>t<<1500>> - \langle
\theta\rangle+ \langle\theta\rangle- \theta)^<<1501>>2<<1501>> \right\rangle dt<<1792>> = \frac
<<1502>>1<<1502>><<1503>>\Delta<<1503>>\int_<<1504>>0<<1504>>^<<1505>>\Delta<<1505>>\left\langle <<1837>>\left(  <<1793>>\lambda_<<1506>>t<<1506>> - \langle
\theta\rangle<<1793>> \right)  ^<<1507>>2<<1507>> <<1837>> \right\rangle \, dt - \left\langle <<1794>>\left(
<<1508>>\theta- \langle\theta\rangle<<1508>> \right)  ^<<1509>>2<<1509>> <<1794>> \right\rangle . \label<<1510>>MISE3<<1510>><tex2html_comment_mark>1890
\end<<1511>>equation<<1511>>
The first term in Eq.~\ref<<1512>>MISE3<<1512>> represents a mean squared fluctuation of the
underlying rate \begin<<2920>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2920>>$\lambda_<<1513>>t<<1513>> $\end<<2921>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2921>>\space from the mean rate \begin<<2922>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2922>>$\left\langle \theta
\right\rangle $\end<<2923>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2923>>, and is independent of the bin size \begin<<2924>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2924>>$\Delta$\end<<2925>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2925>>, because
\begin<<1514>>equation<<1514>>
\frac<<1515>>1<<1515>><<1516>>\Delta<<1516>>\int_<<1517>>0<<1517>>^<<1518>>\Delta<<1518>>\left\langle <<1838>>\left(  <<1795>>\lambda_<<1519>>t<<1519>> -
\langle\theta\rangle<<1795>> \right)  ^<<1520>>2<<1520>> <<1838>> \right\rangle \, dt = \frac<<1521>>1<<1521>><<1522>>T<<1522>>
\int_<<1523>>0<<1523>>^<<1524>>T<<1524>> \left(  <<1796>>\lambda_<<1525>>t<<1525>> - \langle\theta\rangle<<1796>> \right)  ^<<1526>>2<<1526>> \, dt.
\label<<1527>>variance_rate<<1527>><tex2html_comment_mark>1891
\end<<1528>>equation<<1528>>
We define a cost function by subtracting this term from the original MISE,
\begin<<1529>>align<<1529>>
C_<<1530>>n<<1530>>(\Delta)  ;SPMamp;  \equiv\mbox<<1531>>MISE<<1531>> - \frac<<1532>>1<<1532>><<1533>>T<<1533>> \int_<<1534>>0<<1534>>^<<1535>>T<<1535>> \left(
<<1797>>\lambda_<<1536>>t<<1536>> - \langle\theta\rangle<<1797>> \right)  ^<<1537>>2<<1537>> \, dt\nonumber\\ 
;SPMamp;  = \left\langle E(\hat\theta- \theta)^<<1538>>2<<1538>> \right\rangle - \left\langle
<<1798>>\left(  <<1539>>\theta- \langle\theta\rangle<<1539>> \right)  ^<<1540>>2<<1540>> <<1798>> \right\rangle .
\label<<1541>>cost<<1541>><tex2html_comment_mark>1892
\end<<1542>>align<<1542>>
This cost function corresponds to the `risk function' in the report by Rudemo,
(Eq.~2.3), obtained by direct decomposition of the MISE~\cite<<1543>>Rudemo82<<1543>>. The
second term in Eq.~\ref<<1544>>cost<<1544>> represents the temporal fluctuation of the
expected mean rate \begin<<2926>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2926>>$\theta$\end<<2927>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2927>>\space for individual intervals of period \begin<<2928>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2928>>$\Delta$\end<<2929>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2929>>. As
the expected mean rate \begin<<2930>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2930>>$\theta$\end<<2931>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2931>>\space is not an observable quantity, we have to
replace the fluctuation of the expected mean rate with that of the observable
estimator \begin<<2932>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2932>>$\hat<<1545>>\theta<<1545>>$\end<<2933>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2933>>. Using the decomposition rule for an unbiased
estimator (\begin<<2934>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2934>>$E\hat<<1546>>\theta<<1546>>=\theta)$\end<<2935>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2935>>,
\begin<<1547>>equation<<1547>>
\label<<1548>>varLambdah<<1548>>\left\langle E ( <<1549>>\hat\theta- \langle E\hat\theta\rangle<<1549>>
)^<<1550>>2<<1550>> \right\rangle = \left\langle E ( \hat\theta- \theta)^<<1551>>2<<1551>> \right\rangle +
\left\langle <<1799>>\left(  <<1552>>\theta- \langle\theta\rangle<<1552>> \right)  ^<<1553>>2<<1553>> <<1799>>
\right\rangle ,
\end<<1554>>equation<<1554>>
the cost function is transformed into
\begin<<1555>>equation<<1555>>
C_<<1556>>n<<1556>>\left(  \Delta\right)  = 2 \left\langle E (\hat\theta- \theta)^<<1557>>2<<1557>>
\right\rangle - \left\langle E ( <<1558>>\hat\theta- \langle E\hat\theta\rangle<<1558>>
)^<<1559>>2<<1559>> \right\rangle . \label<<1560>>Cn<<1560>><tex2html_comment_mark>1893
\end<<1561>>equation<<1561>>
\begin<<3406>>tex2html_deferred<<3406>>\par\end<<3407>>tex2html_deferred<<3407>>
Due to the assumed Poisson nature of the point process, the number of spikes
\begin<<2936>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2936>>$k$\end<<2937>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2937>>\space counted in each bin obeys a Poisson distribution; the variance of \begin<<2938>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2938>>$k$\end<<2939>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2939>>\space is
equal to the mean. For the estimated rate defined as \begin<<2940>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2940>>$\hat<<1562>>\theta<<1562>><tex2html_comment_mark>1894
=k/(n\Delta)$\end<<2941>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2941>>, this variance-mean relation corresponds to
\begin<<1563>>equation<<1563>>
E (\hat\theta- \theta)^<<1564>>2<<1564>> = \frac<<1565>>1<<1565>><<1566>>n\Delta<<1566>>E <<1567>>\hat\theta<<1567>> .
\label<<1568>>eq:variancemean<<1568>><tex2html_comment_mark>1895
\end<<1569>>equation<<1569>>
By incorporating Eq.~\ref<<1570>>eq:variancemean<<1570>> into Eq.~\ref<<1571>>Cn<<1571>>, the cost
function is given as a function of the estimator \begin<<2942>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2942>>$\hat<<1572>>\theta<<1572>>$\end<<2943>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2943>>,
\begin<<1573>>equation<<1573>>
C_<<1574>>n<<1574>>\left(  \Delta\right)  = \frac<<1575>>2<<1575>><<1800>><<1576>>n\Delta<<1576>><<1800>> \left\langle E \hat
\theta\right\rangle - \left\langle E ( <<1577>>\hat\theta- \langle E\hat\theta
\rangle<<1577>> )^<<1578>>2<<1578>> \right\rangle . \label<<1579>>eq:CostEstimated<<1579>><tex2html_comment_mark>1896
\end<<1580>>equation<<1580>>
The optimal bin size is obtained by minimizing the cost function \begin<<2944>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2944>>$C_<<1581>>n<<1581>>
(\Delta)$\end<<2945>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2945>>, as
\begin<<1582>>equation<<1582>>
\Delta^<<1583>>*<<1583>> \equiv\arg\min_<<1584>>\Delta<<1584>>C_<<1585>>n<<1585>>(\Delta). \label<<1586>>eq: optbinsize<<1586>><tex2html_comment_mark>1897
\end<<1587>>equation<<1587>>
By replacing the expectation with the sample spike count, the cost function
(Eq.~\ref<<1588>>eq:CostEstimated<<1588>>) is converted into a useful recipe, summarized as
`Algorithm 1.'
\begin<<3408>>tex2html_deferred<<3408>>\par\end<<3409>>tex2html_deferred<<3409>>
\begin<<1589>>quote<<1589>>
\textbf<<1590>>Algorithm 1: A method for bin size selection for a Bar-PSTH<<1590>> \vskip1mm
\begin<<3410>>tex2html_deferred<<3410>>\hrule\end<<3411>>tex2html_deferred<<3411>>width \textwidth
\begin<<3412>>tex2html_deferred<<3412>>\par\end<<3413>>tex2html_deferred<<3413>>
\end<<1591>>quote<<1591>>
\begin<<3414>>tex2html_deferred<<3414>>\par\end<<3415>>tex2html_deferred<<3415>>
\begin<<1592>>enumerate<<1592>>
\item <<1593>><<1593>>[(i)]
\begin<<3416>>tex2html_deferred<<3416>>\par\end<<3417>>tex2html_deferred<<3417>>
\item Divide the observation period \begin<<2946>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2946>>$T$\end<<2947>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2947>>\space into \begin<<2948>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2948>>$N$\end<<2949>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2949>>\space bins of width \begin<<2950>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2950>>$\Delta$\end<<2951>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2951>>, and
count the number of spikes \begin<<2952>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2952>>$k_<<1594>>i<<1594>>$\end<<2953>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2953>>\space from all \begin<<2954>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2954>>$n$\end<<2955>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2955>>\space sequences that enter the \begin<<2956>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2956>>$i$\end<<2957>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2957>>th bin.
\begin<<3418>>tex2html_deferred<<3418>>\par\end<<3419>>tex2html_deferred<<3419>>
\item Construct the mean and variance of the number of spikes \begin<<2958>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2958>>$\{k_<<1595>>i<<1595>>\}$\end<<2959>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2959>>\space as,
\begin<<1987>>displaymath<<1987>>
\bar<<1596>>k<<1596>>\equiv\frac<<1597>>1<<1597>><<1598>>N<<1598>>\sum_<<1599>>i=1<<1599>>^<<1600>>N<<1600>>k_<<1601>>i<<1601>>\mbox<<1602>>, and <<1602>>\displaystyle
v\equiv\frac<<1603>>1<<1603>><<1604>>N<<1604>>\sum_<<1605>>i=1<<1605>>^<<1606>>N<<1606>>(k_<<1607>>i<<1607>>-\bar<<1608>>k<<1608>>)^<<1609>>2<<1609>>.
\end<<2040>>displaymath<<2040>>
\begin<<3420>>tex2html_deferred<<3420>>\par\end<<3421>>tex2html_deferred<<3421>>
\end<<1610>>enumerate<<1610>>
\begin<<3422>>tex2html_deferred<<3422>>\par\end<<3423>>tex2html_deferred<<3423>>
Compute the cost function,
\begin<<1988>>displaymath<<1988>>
C_<<1611>>n<<1611>>(\Delta)=\frac<<1801>>2\bar<<1612>>k<<1612>>-v<<1801>><<1802>>(n\Delta)^<<1613>>2<<1613>><<1802>>.
\end<<2041>>displaymath<<2041>>
\begin<<3424>>tex2html_deferred<<3424>>\par\end<<3425>>tex2html_deferred<<3425>>
\begin<<1614>>enumerate<<1614>>
\item Repeat i through iii while changing the bin size \begin<<2960>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2960>>$\Delta$\end<<2961>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2961>>\space to search for
\begin<<2962>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2962>>$\Delta^<<1615>>\ast<<1615>>$\end<<2963>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2963>>\space that minimizes \begin<<2964>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2964>>$C_<<1616>>n<<1616>>(\Delta)$\end<<2965>>tex2html_wrap_inline<<2965>>.
\end<<1617>>enumerate<<1617>>
\begin<<3426>>tex2html_deferred<<3426>>\par\end<<3427>>tex2html_deferred<<3427>>
